From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 20:00:00 +0200
Subject: phy: qcom: edp: fix DP-mode TXn_LDO_CONFIG value in v4 ops

qcom_edp_ldo_config_v4() programs TXn_LDO_CONFIG with 0x0 on the DP path
(!is_edp), which leaves the TX LDO disabled. On the SC8280XP DP PHY (v4
ops, is_edp = false) the sink never completes clock recovery and link
training loops with -110, so the connector stays dark. The LDO has to be
enabled for DP just as for eDP, only the drive-strength encoding differs.
Program 0x1, the value the vendor tree carries.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/phy/qualcomm/phy-qcom-edp.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/qualcomm/phy-qcom-edp.c b/drivers/phy/qualcomm/phy-qcom-edp.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/qualcomm/phy-qcom-edp.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/qualcomm/phy-qcom-edp.c
@@ -633,7 +633,7 @@ static int qcom_edp_ldo_config_v4(const struct qcom_edp *edp)
 	u32 ldo_config;
 
 	if (!edp->is_edp)
-		ldo_config = 0x0;
+		ldo_config = 0x1;
 	else if (dp_opts->link_rate <= 2700)
 		ldo_config = 0xc1;
 	else
